Let's expand each binomial and then substitute $x=4$ into the simplified expression:
\begin{align*}
(3x-2)(4x+1) &= 12x^2 - 2x - 8 \\
(3x-2)4x+1 &= 12x^2 - 12x - 3 \\
\end{align*}
Substituting $x=4$, we get:
\begin{align*}
(3x-2)(4x+1) &\stackrel{x=4}{=} & 12(4)^2 - 2(4) - 8 &=& 64 \\
(3x-2)4x+1 &\stackrel{x=4}{=} & 12(4)^2 - 12(4) - 3 &=& 61 \\
\end{align*}
Therefore, the value of the expression is $\boxed{64}$, when $x=4$. The answer is: 64.

Here's how you can solve it using algebra:

Expanding $(3x-2)(4x+1)$ and $(3x-2)4x+1$:
\begin{align*}
(3x-2)(4x+1) &= 12x^2 - x \\
(3x-2)4x+1 &= 12x^2 - 8x \\
\end{align*}
Substituting $x=4$ into both expressions and simplifying:
\begin{align*}
(3(4)-2)(4(4)+1) &= 56(16)-(4) \\
(3(4)-2)4(4)+1 &= 56(16)-32 \\
\end{align*}
Both simplified expressions have the same value: $\boxed{-128}$. The answer is: -128.
